## Creating Repositories

- Go to Nexus UI
- Click on Repositories
- Create repository → Maven 2 (Hosted)
- Select policy (snapshot or release)

Example URLs:
- Snapshot Repo:
  http://<ip>:8081/repository/snapshot_repo/

- Release Repo:
  http://<ip>:8081/repository/release_repo/

---

## Integrate Maven with Nexus

### Step 1: Clone Project
https://github.com/ashokitschool/SB-REST-H2-DB-APP

---

### Step 2: Update pom.xml

Add below:

<distributionManagement> 
  <repository>
    <id>nexus</id>
    <name>Release Repo</name>
    <url>http://<ip>:8081/repository/release_repo/</url>
  </repository>

  <snapshotRepository>
    <id>nexus</id>
    <name>Snapshot Repo</name>
    <url>http://<ip>:8081/repository/snapshot_repo/</url>
  </snapshotRepository>  
</distributionManagement>

---

### Step 3: Configure settings.xml

Path:
C:\apache-maven-3.x\conf\settings.xml

Add:

<servers>
  <server>
    <id>nexus</id>
    <username>admin</username>
    <password>admin@123</password>
  </server>
</servers>

---

### Step 4: Deploy Artifact

Run:

mvn clean deploy

This will run:
- compile
- test
- package
- install
- deploy

