## Remote Repository (Shared Libraries)

Remote repository is used to store common JAR files used in multiple projects.

---

### Create Remote Repository

- Go to Nexus → Repositories
- Create → Maven (Hosted)
- Give name (example: remote-repo)

---

### Upload JAR

Provide:
- groupId
- artifactId
- version

Example:
groupId: in.ashokit  
artifactId: pwd-utils  
version: RELEASE-1.0  

---

### Add Dependency in pom.xml

<dependency>
  <groupId>in.ashokit</groupId>
  <artifactId>pwd-utils</artifactId>
  <version>RELEASE-1.0</version>
</dependency>

---

### Add Repository in pom.xml

<repositories>
  <repository>
    <id>nexus</id>
    <url>http://<ip>:8081/repository/remote-repo/</url>
  </repository>
</repositories>

---

### Run Build

mvn clean package

---

## Fix HTTP Block Issue

Update settings.xml:

<mirror>
  <id>maven-default-http-blocker</id>
  <mirrorOf>dummy</mirrorOf>
  <url>http://0.0.0.0/</url>
  <blocked>false</blocked>
</mirror>

